  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "In geth:\n\n```\n> 29714174079724412745887019504253973571029824035614949642323418802670541573197\n2.9714174079724414e+76\n```\n\nAnd then if I paste that result into ipython:\n\n```\nIn [1]: int(2.9714174079724414e+76)\nOut[1]: 29714174079724414182345292595171428140511169245030622933092435559513436717056L\n```\n\nThe numbers start out the same, but then notice how they start diverging. I imagine that has something to do with this issue: https://stackoverflow.com/questions/307179/what-is-javascripts-highest-integer-value-that-a-number-can-go-to-without-losin\n\nThis is a problem because it makes it difficult to send large integer literals to contracts.\n\n```\n$ apt-cache show geth | grep Version\nVersion: 1.0.1+46trusty-0ubuntu1\n```\n",
