    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "This is a known issue with JavaScript in general. All JavaScript numbers are 64 bit floats. Maybe the designers of JS thought that this would simplify things.\n\nweb3.js solves this problem using bignumber.js. Please check [the wiki page about web3.js](https://github.com/ethereum/wiki/wiki/JavaScript-API#a-note-on-big-numbers-in-web3js) for more information.\n",
